From: Juniper Bevensee <juniperbevensee@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 12:25:38 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 27/27] feat(signal): auto-detect group creation via
 syncMessage

When the bot is a founding member of a new Signal group, signal-cli sends
a syncMessage with a top-level groupV2 field instead of a regular invite
envelope. Previously this was dropped at the early return. Now we detect
groupV2 inside syncMessage and promote it to the envelope level so the
existing group invite handler (policy check, joinGroup RPC, runtime
allowlist update) processes it.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
